    narr:Claim_ReachabilityAsKeystonePromise skos:note "This framing is a principle candidate that would partially supersede existing category definitions (Curated Expertise, Delegation) by adding a 'promise' layer above the 'mechanism' layer. PROMOTED (2026-04-21): Tony Maley's strong reaction ('Yeah, I like that. I like that a lot. That's perfect. That is perfect, actually. I really like that.') confirms this as the narrative anchor for the sales motion. Conviction promoted from Stake to Boulder. The phrase originated from Scarlet's desire to invert the AI interruption pattern — agent acts on her behalf, receives all messages, only interrupts when it genuinely needs her contribution." .
  }
}
